data.chText: 差别；差异；不同（之处）；变化（之处）
data.enText: the way in which two people or things are not like each other; the way in which sb/sth has changed

data.chText: 这两国的教育制度没有大的差别。
data.enText: There are no significant differences between the education systems of the two countries.

data.chText: 他在研究人和动物之间错综复杂的相似与不同之处。
data.enText: He was studying the complex similarities and differences between humans and animals.

data.chText: 结果没有差别。
data.enText: There's no difference in the results.

data.chText: 她第二次来访时注意到孩子们发生了明显的变化。
data.enText: She noticed a marked difference in the children on her second visit.

data.chText: 我从来都分不清这对双胞胎。
data.enText: I can never tell the difference (= distinguish) between the twins.

data.chText: 喜欢一个人和爱一个人有天壤之别。
data.enText: There's a world of difference between liking someone and loving them.

data.chText: 真是判若两人！你梳这种发型显得太帅了。
data.enText: What a difference! You look great with your hair like that.

data.chText: 差；差额
data.enText: the amount that sth is greater or smaller than sth else

data.chText: 这两种计算机价格上没有多大的差别。
data.enText: There's not much difference in price between the two computers.

data.chText: 这两个男孩的年龄相差六岁。
data.enText: There's an age difference of six years between the boys (= one is six years older than the other) .

data.chText: 我借给你500英镑，其余的你自己解决。
data.enText: I'll lend you £500 and you'll have to find the difference (= the rest of the money that you need) .

data.chText: 我们测量了温度的变化。
data.enText: We measured the difference in temperature.

data.chText: 意见分歧；不和
data.enText: a disagreement between people

data.chText: 我们之间虽然不和，但她仍旧是我的妹妹。
data.enText: We have our differences , but she's still my sister.

data.chText: 你们为什么不消除隔阂，言归于好呢？
data.enText: Why don't you settle your differences and be friends again?

data.chText: 在谁获胜的问题上发生了争执。
data.enText: There was a difference of opinion over who had won.
make a, no, some, etc. difference (to/in sb/sth)

data.chText: 有（或没有、有些等）作用，关系，影响
data.enText: to have an effect/no effect on sb/sth

data.chText: 这场雨对比赛没多大影响。
data.enText: The rain didn't make much difference to the game.

data.chText: 你能否得到这工作应该与你的年龄无关。
data.enText: Your age shouldn't make any difference to whether you get the job or not.

data.chText: 转学对我的一生有着重大影响。
data.enText: Changing schools made a big difference to my life.

data.chText: 他知不知道有什么关系吗？
data.enText: What difference will it make if he knows or not?

data.chText: 我认为颜色无关紧要。
data.enText: I don't think it makes a lot of difference what colour it is (= it is not important) .

data.chText: “我们星期五还是星期六去？”“我无所谓。”
data.enText: ‘Shall we go on Friday or Saturday?’ ‘It makes no difference (to me).’
make all the difference (to sb/sth)

data.chText: 关系重大；大不相同；使更好受
data.enText: to have an important effect on sb/sth; to make sb feel better

data.chText: 在适当的时候说几句体贴话效果迥然不同。
data.enText: A few kind words at the right time make all the difference.
same difference

data.chText: 差不多一样
data.enText: used to say that you think the differences between two things are not important

data.chText: “那不是木琴而是钟琴。” “反正都差不多。”
data.enText: ‘That's not a xylophone, it's a glockenspiel.’ ‘Same difference.’
with a difference

data.chText: 引人注目；与众不同
data.enText: used to show that sth is interesting or unusual

data.chText: 这个跟传统背包不同——它防水。
data.enText: The traditional backpack with a difference─it's waterproof.
bury the hatchet
bury your differences

data.chText: 消除隔阂（重归于好）
data.enText: to stop being unfriendly and become friends again
sink your differences

data.chText: 摒弃分歧；搁置歧见
data.enText: to agree to forget about your disagreements
split the difference

data.chText: （讲价等）各让一步，折中
data.enText: (when discussing a price, etc.) to agree on an amount that is at an equal distance between the two amounts that have been suggested
a/the world of difference

data.chText: 完全不同；是两码事
data.enText: used to emphasize how much difference there is between two things

data.chText: 喜欢一个人和爱一个人完全不是一回事。
data.enText: There's a world of difference between liking someone and loving them.

tr: the quality of being unlike or dissimilar
example: there are many differences between jazz and rock

tr: a disagreement or argument about something important
example: he had a dispute with his wife
the familiar conflict between Republicans and Democrats

tr: a variation that deviates from the standard or norm
the number that remains after subtraction
the number that when added to the subtrahend gives the minuend

example: the difference in her is amazing
his support made a real difference

value.def: The difference between two things is the way in which they are unlike each other.

example.ex: That is the fundamental difference between the two societies...
example.tran: 那是这两个社会之间的根本性差异。

example.ex: There is no difference between the sexes.
We do have social problems here. The difference is the people know each other and try to help each other.
example.tran: 我们这里确实也存在社会问题。所不同的是人们都互相认识而且尽力互相帮助。

value.def: A difference between two quantities is the amount by which one quantity is less than the other.
If people have their differences about something, they disagree about it.

example.ex: The two communities are learning how to resolve their differences.
example.tran: 这两个社群正在学着如何解决彼此之间的分歧。

value.def: If something makes a difference or makes a lot of difference, it affects you and helps you in what you are doing. If something makes no difference, it does not have any effect on what you are doing.

example.ex: Where you live can make such a difference to the way you feel...
example.tran: 住在哪里会极大地影响你的感受。

example.ex: His retirement won't make any difference to the way we conduct our affairs.
example.tran: 他的退休不会影响我们处理事情的方式。

value.def: If you split the difference with someone, you agree on an amount or price which is halfway between two suggested amounts or prices.

example.ex: Shall we split the difference and say $7,500?
example.tran: 我们折中一下，7,500 美元怎么样？

value.tran: （在数量、价格上）折中，各让一步

value.def: If you describe a job or holiday, for example, as a job with a difference or a holiday with a difference, you mean that the job or holiday is very interesting and unusual.

example.ex: For a beach resort with a difference, try Key West.
example.tran: 如果想去一个与众不同的海滨度假胜地，那就去基韦斯特吧。

value.tran: 非常有趣的;与众不同的

value.def: If there is a difference of opinion between two or more people or groups, they disagree about something.

example.ex: Was there a difference of opinion over what to do with the Nobel Prize money?
example.tran: 在如何利用那笔诺贝尔奖金的问题上有不同意见吗？

partsOfSpeech.dec: dif 不，否定 + fic 做 + ult → 不好做 → 困难的
dif 不，否定 + fid 相信 + ent 关于…的 → 不相信〔自己〕的 → 自卑的
dif 分开 + fer 带来 → 分开带来 → 不同
dif 分开 + flu 流 + ence 表状态 → 分开流 → 分流
dif 分开 + fus 流 + e → 使散开流 → 撒播
con 共同 + flu 流 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 流到一起 → 汇流
depend 依靠 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 依靠
differ 不同 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 差异
emerge 出现 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 出现
in 无 + noc 伤害 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 没有伤害 → 无罪
insist 坚持 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 坚持
neg 不 + lig 选择 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 不加选择 → 疏忽
revere 尊敬 + ence 性质，状态，行为 → 尊敬
